ed%20into%20the%20world's%20most%20severe%20humanitarian%20emergency%2C%20affecting%2030%20million%20individuals%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20Sudan's%20population.%20More%20than%2014%20million%E2%80%94over%20a%20quarter%20of%20Sudanese%E2%80%94have%20been%20displaced%2C%20including%20nearly%203.5%20million%20forced%20to%20seek%20refuge%20in%20the%20neighbouring%20countries.%20The%20number%20of%20casualties%20is%20put%20at%20a%20minimum%20of%2020%2C000.%20However%2C%20given%20the%20wide%20extent%20of%20undocumented%2C%20no-holds-barred%20brutality%20unleashed%20by%20the%20conflict%2C%20the%20actual%20figure%20may%20well%20be%20many%20times%20higher.%20In%20economic%20terms%2C%20the%20losses%20are%20put%20at%20%2415%20billion%20and%20the%20national%20GDP%20is%20expected%20to%20decline%20by%2048%25%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20It%20All%20Started%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELarge%20and%20multi-ethnic%20Sudan%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20civil%20strife%20and%20misgovernance.%20Since%20independence%20in%201956%2C%20the%20country%20has%20had%2015%20military%20coups%20and%20two%20civil%20wars%20that%20killed%201.5%20million%20people%20and%20resulted%20in%20the%20eventual%20secession%20of%20South%20Sudan%20in%202011.%20For%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20a%20conflict%20in%20the%20western%20region%20of%20Darfur%20has%20been%20waged%20by%20the%20infamous%20Janjaweed%20militia%20against%20local%20non-Arab%20Muslims%2C%20cumulatively%20killing%20over%202%20lakh%20people%20and%20displacing%20two%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20genesis%20of%20the%20current%20crisis%20lies%20in%20the%2030%20years%20of%20autocracy%20by%20dictator%20Omar%20Hassan%20al-Bashir.%20He%20was%20overthrown%20in%20a%20military%20coup%20in%20April%202019%20after%20months%20of%20popular%20protests.%20The%20Transitional%20Military%20Council%20signed%20framework%20agreements%20with%20citizens'%20groups%20to%20create%20a%20joint%20military-civilian%20sovereignty%20council%20and%20draft%20a%20new%20constitution.%20However%2C%20this%20civilian-military%20cohabitation%20collapsed%20after%20wobbling%20for%20two%20years.%20A%20military%20coup%20followed%20in%20October%202021%20that%20installed%20Gen.%20Abdel%20Fattah%20al-Burhan%2C%20Chief%20of%20Sudan%20Armed%20Forces%20(SAF)%2C%20as%20the%20head%20of%20state.%20Although%20street%20protests%20demanding%20complete%20civilian%20rule%20and%20international%20pressures%20revived%20a%20power-sharing%20framework%2C%20it%20fared%20no%20better.%20Simultaneously%2C%20the%20hitherto%20autonomous%20Rapid%20Support%20Force%20(RSF)%2C%20a%20para-military%20militia%20led%20by%20Gen%20Mohammed%20Hamdan%20Dagalo%2C%20rejected%20the%20December%202022%20draft%20framework%20and%20proposed%20its%20integration%20into%20the%20SAF%2C%20thus%20pushing%20the%20multi-pronged%20chaos%20over%20the%20edge.%20On%20April%2015%2C%202023%2C%20an%20armed%20conflict%20ensued%20between%20an%20estimated%203%2C00%2C000-strong%20SAF%20and%20the%20RSF%2C%20which%20had%20nearly%201%2C00%2C000%20well-armed%20fighters.%20Beneath%20the%20ideological%20and%20ethnic%20trappings%20are%20the%20unadulterated%20ambitions%20of%20the%20two%20warlords.%20The%20ongoing%20mayhem%20has%20completely%20drowned%20the%20raison%20d'etre%20of%20the%20crisis%3A%20the%20demand%20for%20civilian%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Ceasefires%20Have%20Held%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bitter%20and%20bloody%20civil%20war%20in%20Sudan%20has%20defied%20several%20peace-making%20attempts%20in%20Jeddah%2C%20Doha%2C%20Geneva%20and%20elsewhere.%20Even%20the%20short-term%20ceasefires%20have%20not%20held.%20For%20the%20initial%20few%20months%2C%20the%20hostilities%20remained%20inconclusive%20and%20the%20foreign%20involvement%20was%20low.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20the%20SAF%20seems%20to%20have%20got%20the%20upper%20hand.%20It%20has%20recently%20notched%20several%20successes%20against%20the%20RSF%20in%20the%20centre%20and%20adjoining%20southern%20areas.%20It%20has%20retaken%20most%20of%20the%20national%20capital%20Khartoum-Omdurman%20and%20has%20wrested%20Wadi%20al-Madani%3Cem%3E%20(see%20map%20below)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20al-Gazeera%20province%2C%20a%20strategically%20important%20cross-road%20and%20the%20country's%20bread-basket.%20However%2C%20the%20RSF%20still%20controls%20the%20vast%20region%20of%20Darfur%20in%20the%20west%2C%20where%20the%20SAF's%20solitary%20perch%20at%20el-Fasher%20is%20under%20its%20siege.%20It%20also%20has%20a%20hold%20on%20West%20Kordofan%20province%20bordering%20South%20Sudan%2C%20which%20was%20ceded%20as%20a%20separate%20country%20in%202011%20after%20decades%20of%20civil%20war.%20Several%20other%20areas%20of%20Sudan%20are%20either%20under%20contestation%20or%20are%20under%20the%20control%20of%20independent%20tribal%20militias%20with%20shifting%20loyalties.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Sudan's%20national%20army%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20retaking%20the%20capital%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flh7-rt.googleusercontent.com%2Fdocsz%2FAD_4nXe4weUpFLugTCIfNpJngGZGvJGonDCU2ULDLXaIGJU1idnqRoYEeHN7dhbjR1eeGS_ln2dqK_oIMCZKmwyG8U6fI3liRz1XFxdjm-8KOUCH_k34R7pxWZvWoDNGw3Qnkl6BtaDXh_ibGrBMLd-TBo8%3Fkey%3DrlCrwJnvhClB_jqqaZK7LYL4%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22732%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPretending%20To%20Speak%20For%20Sudan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20military%20situation%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20geopolitical%20alignments%20predicate%20a%20de%20facto%20partition%20of%20the%20country.%20This%20shift%20seems%20to%20have%20prompted%20both%20sides%20to%20unveil%20their%20respective%20plans%20to%20lure%20uncommitted%20stakeholders%E2%80%94both%20domestic%20and%20foreign-based.%20In%20late%20February%2C%20the%20RSF%20and%20its%20allies%20signed%20a%20%E2%80%98founding%20charter'%20of%20a%20breakaway%20government%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98New%20Sudan'%2C%20designed%20to%20pull%20legitimacy%20from%20the%20existing%20army-led%20government%20and%20facilitate%20advanced%20arms%20imports.%20The%20%E2%80%98new%20constitution'%20formally%20establishes%20a%20government%20and%20maps%20out%20what%20it%20describes%20as%20a%20federal%2C%20secular%20state%2C%20split%20into%20eight%20regions.%20Although%20the%20RSF%20and%20its%20allies%20have%20said%20the%20government%20will%20be%20formed%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20it%20is%20still%20unclear%20who%20will%20be%20in%20it%20or%20where%20it%20will%20operate%20from.%20The%20SAF-led%20junta%20has%20countered%20these%20moves%20by%20announcing%20on%20February%2025%20that%20its%20plan%20envisages%20forming%20a%20transitional%20government%20under%20a%20civilian%20prime%20minister%20and%20initiating%20a%20national%20dialogue%20with%20political%20and%20civil%20society%20groups%2C%20eventually%20leading%20to%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%20On%20March%2013%2C%20the%20Sudanese%20Foreign%20Minister%20claimed%20that%20consultations%20have%20begun%20to%20launch%20an%20inclusive%20political%20process%20aimed%20at%20forming%20a%20technocratic%20government%20to%20lead%20the%20country%20through%20the%20transitional%20period%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20reconstruction.%20Needless%20to%20add%2C%20both%20these%20warring%20factions%20pretend%20to%20speak%20for%20Sudan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20A%20Partition%20Could%20Be%20Dangerous%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20international%20community%20has%20reacted%20warily%20to%20these%20announcements.%20In%20a%20statement%20on%20March%205%2C%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfounding%20charter%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20it%20could%20worsen%20an%20%E2%80%9Calready%20dire%20humanitarian%20situation%E2%80%9D.%20On%20March%2012%2C%20the%20African%20Union%20reiterated%20its%20warning%20that%20the%20move%20to%20form%20a%20parallel%20government%20by%20the%20RSF%20posed%20%E2%80%9Ca%20huge%20risk%20of%20the%20partitioning%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20It%20urged%20all%20of%20its%20member%20states%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20international%20community%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20recognise%20any%20government%20or%20parallel%20entity%20aimed%20at%20partitioning%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20Republic%20of%20Sudan%20or%20its%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%20The%20EU%20also%20reiterated%20its%20commitment%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunity%20and%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20Sudan%E2%80%9D.%20These%20foreign%20stakeholders%20seemed%20to%20be%20persuaded%20against%20the%20RSF%20move%20in%20light%20of%20the%20disastrous%20partition%20of%20neighbouring%20Libya.%20The%20stakeholders%20also%20worry%20that%20a%20fledgling%20state%20comprising%20Darfur%20and%20Kordofan%20would%20exacerbate%20the%20regional%20fragility.%20It%20would%20be%20at%20war%20with%20the%20SAF%20in%20Khartoum.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20would%20border%20brittle%20states%20such%20as%20Libya%2C%20Chad%2C%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20and%20South%20Sudan%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20facing%20fissiparous%20tendencies.%20Last%20but%20not%20least%2C%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20the%20RSF%2C%20stemming%20mainly%20from%20the%20Arab%20Janjaweed%20militia%2C%20has%20engaged%20in%20pogroms%20against%20the%20African%20tribes%20of%20Darfur.%20These%20activities%20have%20intensified%20during%20two%20years%20of%20civil%20war%2C%20sending%20millions%20of%20refugees%20to%20neighbouring%20countries.%20Creating%20a%20separate%20country%20led%20by%20RSF%20would%20coagulate%20this%20problem.%20Sooner%20than%20later%2C%20these%20temporary%20refugee%20settlements%20would%20become%20the%20breeding%20grounds%20for%20undesirable%20activities%2C%20including%20a%20base%20for%20anti-RSF%20militias.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHoping%20Against%20Hope%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20mainstream%20stakeholders%20have%20been%20against%20the%20repartitioning%20of%20Sudan%2C%20the%20wider%20international%20context%20is%20more%20nuanced.%20The%20Sudanese%20civil%20war%20does%20not%20rank%20high%20on%20the%20priority%20list%20of%20the%20international%20community%2C%20which%20has%20more%20politically%20pressing%20crises%20to%20worry%20about.%20There%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20clear%20division%20among%20the%20various%20regional%20countries.%20The%20SAF-led%20government%20is%20widely%20recognised%20and%20it%20is%20militarily%20supported%20by%20Egypt%2C%20Turkey%20and%20Iran.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20UAE%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20militarily%20backing%20the%20RSF%2C%20even%20as%20Abu%20Dhabi%20stoutly%20denies%20it.%20Its%20motives%20are%20unclear%20and%20could%20range%20from%20profiteering%20from%20smuggled%20gold%20from%20Darfur%20mines%20to%20curbing%20Sudan's%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20Islamic%E2%80%9D%20tendencies%20backing%20the%20SAF.%20Chad%20and%20Gen%20Khalifa%20Haftar's%20Benghazi-based%20government%20in%20Libya%20are%20also%20supporting%20the%20RSF%2C%20which%20reportedly%20continues%20to%20receive%20the%20support%20of%20Russia's%20Wagner%20militia%2C%20disbanded%20two%20years%20ago.%20Further%2C%20there%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20arms%20and%20mercenaries%20from%20the%20global%20grey%20market%20as%20well%20as%20the%20motley%20non-state%20actors%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa.%20The%20resumed%20civil%20wars%20in%20South%20Sudan%20and%20Ethiopia%20and%20instability%20in%20eastern%20Congo%20are%20also%20likely%20to%20cast%20their%20long%20shadows%20on%20Sudan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20some%20observers%20see%20an%20east-west%20partition%20of%20Sudan%20as%20a%20natural%20progression%20in%20the%20unwinnable%20civil%20war.%20They%20expect%20that%20such%20a%20division%20would%20bring%20an%20end%20to%20the%20spread-out%20civil%20war%20that%20has%20devastated%20the%20entire%20country.%20Post-partition%2C%20they%20expect%20the%20two%20sides%20would%20get%20preoccupied%20with%20the%20consolidation%20of%20their%20respective%20fiefs%2C%20the%20physical%20and%20institutional%20reconstruction%2C%20and%20muzzle%20demands%20for%20a%20due%20political%20process%20towards%20democratisation.%20However%2C%20given%20the%20bitter%20legacy%20of%20the%20two%20years%20of%20civil%20war%2C%20such%20sanguinity%20would%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98hoping-against-hope'%20wager%20against%20realism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Mahesh%20Sachdev%20is%20a%20retired%20Indian%20Ambassador%20and%20an%20Arabist.%20He%20currently%20heads%20Eco-Diplomacy%20and%20Strategies%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20consultancy.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742376420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fehg8ip3s_sudan-civil-war-afp_625x300_18_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsudan-is-staring-at-a-second-partition-thanks-to-two-warlords-7958473%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20testimony%20to%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20last%20week%2C%20the%20UNICEF%20chief%20disclosed%20that%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20has%20evolved%20into%20the%20world's%20most%20severe%20humanitarian%20emergency%2C%20affecting%2030%20million%20individuals%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20Sudan's%20population%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IT%20firm%20Happiest%20Minds%20appoints%20Joseph%20Anantharaju%20as%20CEO%2C%20Co-chairman%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742376353000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fit-firm-happiest-minds-appoints-joseph-anantharaju-as-ceo-co-