%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20waive%20a%206-month%20cooling%20period%20post-divorce.%20The%20honourable%20court%C2%A0has%20directed%20the%20family%20court%20to%20decide%20the%20divorce%20plea%20of%20cricketer%20Yuzvendra%20Chahal%20and%20his%20estranged%20wife%20Dhanashree%20Verma%20by%20March%2020%20because%20of%20the%20Punjab%20Kings%20cricketer's%20participation%20in%20the%20Indian%20Premier%20League%20(IPL)%202025%20season%20from%20March%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBar%20and%20Bench%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3A%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EBombay%20High%20Court%20has%20overturned%20a%20Family%20Court%20decision%20that%20denied%20the%20request%20to%20waive%20the%20statutory%20cooling-off%20period%20for%20the%20divorce%20of%20cricketer%20Yuzvendra%20Chahal%20and%20Dhanashree%20Verma%20under%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act.%20A%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Madhav%20Jamdar%20has%20also%20directed%20the%20family%20court%20to%20decide%20the%20divorce%20petition%20by%20tomorrow%20considering%20Chahal's%20participation%20in%20the%20upcoming%20IPL.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FBreaking%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Breaking%3C%2Fa%3E%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20has%20overturned%20a%20Family%20Court%20decision%20that%20denied%20the%20request%20to%20waive%20the%20statutory%20cooling-off%20period%20for%20the%20divorce%20of%20cricketer%20Yuzvendra%20Chahal%20and%20Dhanashree%20Verma%20under%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FBombayHC%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23BombayHC%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FYuzvendraChahal%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23YuzvendraChahal%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F5hdwLFEtIM%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F5hdwLFEtIM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Bar%20and%20Bench%20(%40barandbench)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fbarandbench%2Fstatus%2F1902261160490999826%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2019%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Bar%20and%20Bench%2C%20the%20couple%20that%20got%20married%20in%20December%202020%20has%20been%20living%20apart%20since%20June%202022.%20It%20was%20only%20in%20February%20this%20year%20that%20they%20decided%20to%20file%20a%20divorce%20plea%20before%20the%20Bandra%20Family%20Court.%20The%20couple%20also%20filed%20an%20application%20along%20with%20the%20petition%20to%20waive%20the%20cooling%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Section%2013B(2)%2C%20a%20family%20court%20can%20consider%20a%20mutual%20petition%20for%20divorce%20only%20after%20six%20months%20from%20the%20date%20of%20its%20filing.%20The%20couple%20is%20given%20a%20cooling-off%20period%20in%20order%20to%20explore%20possibilities%20of%20settlement%20and%20reunion.%20But%2C%20with%20Chahal%20and%20Dhanshree%20living%20apart%20from%20each%20other%20for%20more%20than%202%20years%2C%20the%20Bombay%20HC%20didn't%20feel%20that%20the%20cooling-off%20clause%20applied%20in%20this%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20was%20filed%20under%20Section%2013B%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20suggesting%20divorce%20by%20mutual%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20was%20complicated%20when%20the%20court%2C%20on%20February%2020%2C%20refused%20to%20waive%20the%206%20months%20statutory%20cooling%20period%2C%20citing%20partial%20compliance%20with%20regards%20to%20a%20consent%20term%20between%20Chahal%20and%20Dhanashree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20consent%20term%2C%20Chahal%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20permanent%20alimony%20to%20his%20estranged%20wife%20of%20Rs%204%20crore%2075%20lakhs%20to%20Verma.%20However%2C%20the%20cricketer%20is%20said%20to%20have%20only%20paid%20Rs%202%20crore%20