%23%3A~%3Atext%3DElon%2520Musk%2520says%2520sleeping%2520on%2Cpictured%2520sleeping%2520in%2520the%2520office%26amp%3Btext%3DElon%2520Musk%2520talked%2520about%2520his%2Cboss%2520sleeping%2520in%2520the%2520office.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla%20floor%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20he%20used%20to%20sleep%20to%20inspire%20workers%20to%20%26quot%3Bgive%20it%20their%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20is%20continuing%20to%20play%20Donald%20Trump's%20all-powerful%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20buddy%26quot%3B%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20reign%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-downsized-big-tech-tesla-twitter-big-government-trump-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20made%20Tesla%20investors%20want%20their%20CEO%20back.%20But%20he's%20far%20from%20the%20first%20chief%20executive%20to%20go%20AWOL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsent%20leadership%20%26quot%3Bis%20something%20of%20a%20silent%20epidemic%20in%20corporations%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Laura%20McHale%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20professional%20coaching%20firm%20Conduit%20Consultants%20Limited.%20It%20can%20take%20several%20forms%2C%20she%20says%3A%20from%20%26quot%3Bleader%20distance%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20CEOs%20are%20physically%20OOO%20as%20they%20court%20investors%20or%20go%20on%20the%20panel%20circuit%20or%20communicate%20infrequently%2C%20to%20psychological%20neglect%20(lacking%20direction%2C%20not%20delegating%2C%20failing%20to%20give%20employees%20proper%20recognition).%20While%20absenteeism%20is%20quieter%20than%20headline-making%20destructive%20behaviors%20like%20bullying%20or%20abuse%2C%20McHale%20says%20it's%20more%20common%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20just%20as%20harmful%20to%20company%20morale%20and%20productivity.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20yet%2C%20it's%20almost%20never%20talked%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scope%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20hard%20to%20measure%20in%20part%20because%20what%20modern%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-tesla-ceo-job-broken-chief-hypocrisy-officer-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECEOs%20do%20all%20day%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Musk%20included%20%E2%80%94%20is%20somewhat%20of%20a%20mystery.%20Until%20about%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20chief%20executive's%20time%20was%20largely%20trackable%2C%20as%20they%20spent%20most%20of%20their%20day%20closely%20overseeing%20their%20company's%20product.%20But%20as%20mergers%20and%20IPOs%20became%20more%20common%20and%20corporations%20became%20more%20global%2C%20the%20CEO's%20role%20shifted%20from%20an%20internal%20product%20leader%20to%20a%20public%20figure%20aiming%20to%20drive%20shareholder%20value%20on%20the%20world%20stage.%20Today%2C%20many%20top%20CEOs%20jump%20from%20executive%20positions%20at%20companies%20in%20different%20industries%20rather%20than%20working%20their%20way%20up%20and%20learning%20a%20company%20inside%20and%20out.%20As%20they%20focus%20on%20building%20their%20personal%20brand%20or%20even%20working%20with%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20company's%20future%2C%20they%20may%20lose%20sight%20of%20the%20day-to-day%20operations%20that%20build%20strong%20company%20cultures.%20A%202009%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F40506267%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Quarterly%20Journal%20of%20Economics%20found%20that%20as%20CEOs%20become%20superstars%20as%20well-known%20as%20the%20companies%20they%20run%2C%20they%20begin%20to%20underperform.%20The%20%26quot%3Bconsequences%20of%20media-induced%20superstar%20status%20for%20shareholders%20are%20negative%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20at%20smaller%20firms%2C%20leaders'%20attention%20can%20become%20easily%20diverted.%20At%20startups%20in%20particular%2C%20CEOs%20have%20to%20focus%20on%20raising%20money%20and%20pleasing%20investors%2C%20which%20often%20takes%20them%20away%20from%20their%20offices.%20This%20absenteeism%20can%20turn%20%26quot%3Btoxic%2C%26quot%3B%20McHale%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20destructive%20for%20employees%20and%20systems.%20It%20minimizes%20the%20importance%20of%20social%20relationships%20with%20our%20leaders.%26quot%3B%20A%202015%20Interact%2FHarris%20Poll%20of%20US%20workers%20found%20that%20most%20of%20the%20communication%20issues%20people%20had%20with%20their%20company%20leaders%20weren't%20about%20bullying%20or%20demeaning%2C%20but%20about%20what%20their%20bosses%20%3Cem%3Eweren't%3C%2Fem%3E%20doing%3A%20from%20not%20knowing%20employees'%20names%20to%20not%20giving%20clear%20directions%20or%20recognizing%20their%20achievements.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-8551.2009.00672.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202010%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Blaissez-faire%26quot%3B%20leadership%20was%20more%20prevalent%20than%20other%20types%20of%20destructive%20leadership.%20And%20a%20recently%20updated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3761972%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20companies%20whose%20CEOs%20work%20remotely%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20underperform%20and%20have%20lower%20valuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20is%20far%20from%20the%20first%20CEO%20to%20try%20to%20wear%20the%20hat%20in%20two%20places%3A%20Steve%20Jobs%20ran%20Apple%20and%20Pixar%20simultaneously%2C%20and%20Jack%20Dorsey%20oversaw%20Twitter%20and%20Square%20(now%20Block).%20But%20Jobs%20was%20a%20largely%20hands-off%20manager%20at%20Pixar%2C%20delegating%20tasks%20to%20other%20execs.%20Twitter%20has%20always%20been%20difficult%20to%20monetize%20and%20effectively%20moderate%2C%20and%20Dorsey%20stepped%20down%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20much%20as%20there's%20no%20comparison%20for%20Tesla's%20plunge%20in%20value%2C%20Musk%20himself%20is%20incomparable.%20In%20addition%20to%20Tesla%2C%20Musk%20has%20on%20his%20plate%20Neuralink%2C%20X%2C%20The%20Boring%20Company%2C%20SpaceX%2C%20and%20xAI.%20He%20remains%20chief%20executive%20of%20Tesla%2C%20SpaceX%2C%20and%20xAI%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20in%20addition%20to%20posting%20on%20X%20at%20a%20dizzying%20pace%20and%20fathering%2014%20children.%20In%202022%2C%20when%20he%20added%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-elon-musk-startup-competitition-town-square-election-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETwitter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20his%20empire%20of%20influential%20businesses%2C%20some%20management%20experts%20speculated%20that%20he'd%20bitten%20off%20more%20than%20he%20could%20chew.%20Musk%20slashed%20staff%20by%2080%25%20and%20ran%20the%20hobbled%20blue%20bird%20alongside%20his%20other%20companies%20for%20several%20months%20before%20naming%20Linda%20Yaccarino%20as%20CEO.%20A%20radically%20new%20version%20of%20Twitter%2C%20renamed%20X%2C%20still%20worked%2C%20defying%20many%20predictions%20that%20it%20would%20break%20under%20the%20pressure.%20Amid%20his%20X%20takeover%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6243613%2Fwhy-tesla-stock-down%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla's%20stock%20also%20plummeted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20high%20of%20%24309%20a%20share%20in%20September%202022%20to%20a%20low%20of%20%24103%20in%20January%202023%20%E2%80%94%20because%20of%20concerns%20around%20EV%20demand%2C%20rising%20inflation%20and%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20Musk's%20distractions%20at%20Twitter.%20But%20Tesla%20stock%20roared%20back%20through%20the%20rest%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20Musk%20began%20raiding%20the%20federal%20government's%20IT%20system%20in%20the%20name%20of%20cost%20cutting%2C%20many%20were%20slow%20to%20count%20him%20out.%20Perhaps%20he%20could%20bring%20the%20outsider%20energy%20needed%20to%20pare%20down%20bureaucracy%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3Ekeep%20his%20companies%20humming%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20So%20far%2C%20DOGE%20has%20fired%20thousands%20of%20workers%2C%20canceled%20lifesaving%20aid%2C%20and%20produced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanagement-experts-musk-doge-case-study-bad-management-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eall-around%20chaos%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20debate%20how%20well%20Musk's%20tactics%20are%20working%20to%20cut%20government%20waste%2C%20but%20it's%20undeniable%20now%20that%20DOGE%20and%20Musk's%20political%20involvement%20are%20eating%20away%20at%20his%20biggest%20cash%20cow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Tesla%2C%20Musk%20is%20the%20missing%20CEO%20who%20isn't%20really%20missing%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20everywhere%20else.%20He%20dominates%20headlines%20each%20day%2C%20his%20face%20appearing%20constantly%20in%20the%20press%20and%20his%20posts%20gaining%20eyeballs%20all%20over%20X.%20That's%20part%20of%20Tesla's%20problem.%20Owners%20and%20potential%20buyers%20of%20the%20cars%20no%20longer%20can%20separate%20Musk's%20political%20ideology%20from%20the%20brand%2C%20and%20his%20brutal%20cost-cutting%20tactics%20have%20turned%20people%20off.%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20Musk's%20divided%20attention%20and%20political%20unpopularity%20affecting%20the%20once%20premiere%20EV%20company%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-stock-price-outlook-elon-musk-trade-tsla-selloff-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla%20is%20facing%20several%20roadblocks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20increased%20competition%20in%20the%20electric-vehicle%20industry%20from%20Chinese%20manufacturers%20and%20uncertainty%20around%20the%20development%20of%20its%20fully%20autonomous%20self-driving%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJumping%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20daily%20grind%20of%20companies%20%26quot%3Bis%20especially%20problematic%20when%20you're%20a%20micro-manager%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20Yoffie%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20business%20administration%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School.%20We%20know%20that%20Musk%20%26quot%3Blikes%20to%20really%20get%20into%20the%20weeds%20and%20into%20the%20details%2C%26quot%3B%20Yoffie%20notes.%20But%20there%20aren't%20enough%20hours%20in%20a%20day%20to%20micromanage%20a%20handful%20of%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20dive%20deep%20into%20the%20core%20issues%20of%20each.%20In%20January%20and%20February%2C%20Musk%20was%20reportedly%20sleeping%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20his%20DOGE%20office%20across%20the%20street%20from%20the%20White%20House%2C%20adapting%20his%20hardcore%20playbook%20from%20working%20at%20Tesla%20and%20Twitter%20to%20show%20his%20dedication%20at%20DOGE.%20Musk%20traveled%20with%20Trump%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-donald-trump-feud-relationship-timeline-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMar-a-Lago%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20donor%20dinner%20as%20recently%20as%20this%20weekend.%20Following%20the%20election%2C%20he%20spent%20so%20much%20time%20at%20Trump's%20Florida%20oasis%20that%20the%20president%20joked%3A%20%26quot%3BElon%20won't%20go%20home.%20I%20can't%20get%20rid%20of%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20CEOs%20go%20long%20periods%20without%20seeing%20their%20employees%20or%20they%20communicate%20sporadically%20over%20email%20with%20staff%20in%20a%20way%20that%20creates%20more%20separation%20between%20themselves%20and%20workers.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20finger%20on%20the%20pulse%20of%20what's%20really%20going%20on%20in%20their%20organization%2C%20they%20start%20losing%20credibility%20because%20they%20often%20will%20helicopter%20in%2C%20blow%20things%20up%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20create%20a%20big%20kerfuffle%2C%26quot%3B%20Lori%20Dernavich%2C%20an%20executive%20coach%20and%20leadership%20development%20advisor%