t%2C%20which%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20useful%20bargaining%20chip%20in%20his%20negotiations%20with%20sellers.%20He%20didn't%20have%20to%20ask%20sellers%20to%20cover%20his%20agent's%20fee%2C%20which%20allowed%20them%20to%20pocket%20the%20sizable%20chunk%20of%20the%20deal%20that%20they%20would%20have%20otherwise%20had%20to%20fork%20over%20to%20his%20representation.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-san-francisco-to-texas-for-work-life-balance-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epricey%20Bay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20typical%20home%20trades%20for%20north%20of%20%241%20million%2C%20that%20meant%20savings%20of%20%2425%2C000%20or%20more.%20When%20one%20of%20Dutta's%20offers%20eventually%20won%20out%2C%20it%20wasn't%20because%20he%20proposed%20the%20largest%20dollar%20figure%3B%20his%20agent%2C%20Donny%20Suh%2C%20tells%20me%20other%20prospective%20buyers%20came%20in%20higher.%20But%20without%20having%20to%20pay%20out%20a%20commission%20for%20Suh%2C%20the%20seller%20stood%20to%20net%20the%20most%20money%20from%20Dutta's%20offer.%20He%20closed%20on%20the%20three-bedroom%20home%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20has%20left%20Dutta%20with%20some%20what-ifs%20from%20his%20prior%20home%20search.%20He%20recalls%20one%20house%20for%20which%20he%20was%20outbid%20by%20just%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20had%20this%20sort%20of%20tool%20in%20our%20hands%20at%20that%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20wouldn't%20have%20lost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebattle%20over%20commissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20who%20pays%2C%20how%20much%20they%20pay%2C%20and%20when%20the%20money%20changes%20hands%20%E2%80%94%20comes%20down%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20starts%20with%20the%20multiple%20listing%20services%20%E2%80%94%20local%20databases%20where%20most%20homes%20are%20advertised%20for%20sale.%20They%20may%20sound%20like%20unsexy%20infrastructure%2C%20but%20they've%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20propping%20up%20the%20typical%20agent%20commission.%20There%20are%20more%20than%20500%20of%20these%20databases%20around%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20vast%20majority%20are%20operated%20by%20local%20Realtor%20associations%20that%20follow%20rules%20handed%20down%20by%20the%20NAR.%20While%20the%20national%20organization%20didn't%20set%20commissions%20and%20says%20they've%20always%20been%20negotiable%2C%20it%20did%20set%20up%20rules%20that%20helped%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo.%20In%20the%20presettlement%20days%2C%20a%20seller%20who%20listed%20their%20home%20on%20the%20MLS%20had%20to%20fill%20out%20a%20little%20box%20saying%20how%20much%20they'd%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20the%20buyer's%20agent.%20Since%20buyers%20already%20had%20enough%20up-front%20costs%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20everyone%20assumed%20that%20deals%20would%20go%20more%20smoothly%20if%20the%20suddenly%20cash-flush%20seller%20just%20paid%20out%20both%20sides.%20This%20setup%20allowed%20buyers%20to%20basically%20ignore%20how%20much%20their%20agent%20was%20getting%20paid%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20buyers'%20agents%20used%20to%20tell%20clients%20their%20services%20were%20free%20until%20a%20%3Cem%3Edifferent%3C%2Fem%3E%20legal%20battle%20ended%20that%20practice%20in%202020.%20It%20also%20meant%20that%20sellers%20almost%20always%20stuck%20to%20the%20industry%20standard%20of%202.5%25%20or%203%25%20of%20the%20final%20price%20for%20each%20agent%2C%20either%20because%20they%20didn't%20know%20any%20different%20or%20because%20offering%20less%20could%20risk%20being%20passed%20over%20by%20buyers'%20agents%2C%20who%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agent-commissions-steering-hiding-homes-housing-market-lawsuits-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsteer%26quot%3B%20their%20clients%20away%20from%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20lower-than-average%20commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20NAR%2C%20the%20sellers%20who%20sued%20the%20organization%20alleged%20that%20this%20whole%20system%20was%20an%20elaborate%20scheme%20to%20pull%20the%20wool%20over%20regular%20people's%20eyes%20and%20force%20them%20to%20pay%20unfairly%20high%20commissions.%20Given%20that%20the%20median%20home%20price%20in%20the%20US%20is%20about%20%24419%2C000%2C%20a%206%25%20commission%2C%20split%20between%20two%20agents%2C%20would%20mean%20shelling%20out%20more%20than%20%2425%2C000.%20While%20the%20plaintiffs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-antitrust-lawsuits-verdict-agent-commissions-nar-future-homebuying-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushed%20for%20commissions%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bdecoupled%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20paying%20their%20own%20agents%20separately%2C%20the%20%24418%20million%20settlement%20last%20year%20didn't%20go%20quite%20that%20far.%20But%20it%20did%20offer%20enough%20changes%20to%20throw%20the%20real%20estate%20world%20into%20flux.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20change%20is%20that%20sellers%20and%20their%20agents%20can%20no%20longer%20offer%20buyer-agent%20commissions%20through%20the%20MLS.%20In%20theory%2C%20this%20should%20get%20rid%20of%20that%20steering%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20if%20sellers%20aren't%20offering%20a%20commission%2C%20buyers'%20agents%20can't%20direct%20their%20clients%20away%20from%20the%20homes%20with%20less%20than%20the%20customary%20fee.%20But%20there's%20a%20huge%20loophole%20here%3A%20Sellers%20can%20advertise%20a%20buyer-agent%20commission%20pretty%20much%20anywhere%20else%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20broker's%20website%2C%20over%20the%20phone%2C%20on%20sites%20like%20Zillow%20or%20Redfin.%20If%20a%20buyer's%20agent%20wants%20to%20see%20how%20much%20they'll%20make%20off%20a%20home%2C%20it's%20easy%20for%20them%20to%20check.%20Given%20this%20workaround%2C%20many%20sellers%20are%20still%20offering%20to%20pay%20the%20standard%20commission%2C%20which%20makes%20sense%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-sellers-summer-disappointment-mortgage-rates-house-prices-real-estate-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoday's%20slow%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Given%20the%20low%20number%20of%20homes%20changing%20hands%2C%20people%20are%20wary%20of%20doing%20anything%20that%20could%20muck%20up%20a%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20face%20more%20paperwork%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20settlement.%20Before%20an%20agent%20so%20much%20as%20opens%20a%20door%20for%20a%20buyer%20these%20days%2C%20they'll%20have%20to%20get%20them%20to%20sign%20an%20agreement%20stating%20the%20terms%20of%20their%20relationship%2C%20including%20compensation.%20These%20forms%2C%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-homebuying-rule-sign-buyer-representation-agreement-realtors-lawsuit-settlement-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuyer-representation%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20historically%20been%20introduced%20much%20later%20in%20the%20process%2C%20if%20they%20were%20used%20at%20all.%20And%20they%20vary%20widely%20by%20brokerage%20and%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20some%20agreements%20are%20simple%20one-sheeters%20to%20tour%20a%20few%20homes%2C%20while%20others%20lock%20buyers%20into%20exclusive%20arrangements%20for%20months.%20It's%20the%20difference%20between%20seeing%20someone%20casually%20and%20getting%20married%20on%20the%20first%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20at%20least%2C%20the%20combination%20of%20a%20slow%20market%2C%20general%20inertia%2C%20and%20lagging%20consumer%20awareness%20has%20kept%20the%20status%20quo%20relatively%20intact.%20A%20study%20by%20the%20real%20estate%20brokerage%20Redfin%20found%20that%20the%20typical%20buyer-agent%20commission%20was%202.36%25%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%20the%20year%2C%20down%20from%202.43%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20when%20the%20settlement%20was%20announced%2C%20and%20unchanged%20from%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20when%20the%20rules%20went%20into%20effect.%20But%20again%2C%20it's%20still%20pretty%20early%2C%20and%20many%20industry%20insiders%20expect%20the%20changes%20to%20eventually%20start%20knocking%20down%20commissions%20as%20agents%20are%20forced%20to%20compete%20on%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20our%20projection%20still%20hasn't%20changed%20much%2C%20which%20is%2C%20over%20time%2C%20that%20will%20still%20come%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Joe%20Rath%2C%20the%20head%20of%20industry%20relations%20for%20Redfin%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20downward%20pressure%20still%20exists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%2C%20exactly%2C%20could%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20start%20coming%20out%20ahead%3F%20A%20big%20step%20is%20simple%20consumer%20education.%20The%20real%20estate%20firm%20Clever%20surveyed%201%2C000%20homeowners%20and%20prospective%20buyers%20and%20found%20that%20even%20after%20the%20new%20rules%20went%20into%20effect%2C%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20either%20didn't%20understand%20the%20implications%20or%20hadn't%20even%20heard%20of%20the%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOld%20habits%20die%20hard%2C%20especially%20when%20there's%20so%20much%20confusion%20around%20these%20changes.%20And%20critics%20of%20the%20settlement%20say%20it's%20actually%20opened%20up%20new%20pitfalls%20for%20buyers.%20Before%2C%20the%20MLS%20at%20least%20showed%20you%20what%20almost%20every%20home%20was%20offering%20in%20commissions%20%E2%80%94%20now%20that%20kind%20of%20information%20has%20been%20scattered%20or%20isn't%20publicly%20available%20at%20all%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20tell%20whether%20%26quot%3Bsteering%26quot%3B%20is%20happening.%20And%20some%20of%20the%20representation%20agreements%20floating%20around%20could%20end%20up%20locking%20buyers%20into%20exclusive%20relationships%20with%20incompetent%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20these%20deceptive%20practices%20have%20been%20basically%20turned%20underground%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanya%20Monestier%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20at%20Buffalo%2C%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20consumers%20absorb%20these%20new%20rules%20and%20start%20to%20negotiate%20on%20commissions%2C%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20transaction%20stand%20to%20benefit.%20For%20sellers%2C%20the%20main%20advice%20boils%20down%20to%20this%3A%20Don't%20offer%20an%20exact%20commission%20anywhere.%20Not%20on%20the%20MLS%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20also%20not%20on%20a%20broker's%20website%2C%20via%20telephone%2C%20or%20a%20sign%20in%20the%20front%20yard%2C%20Stephen%20Brobeck%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Policy%20Center%2C%20says.%20Instead%2C%20allow%20buyers%20to%20make%20offers%20on%20agent%20payment%2C%20just%20like%20they%20do%20for%20the%20home%20itself.%20One%20buyer%20might%20offer%20to%20pay%202.5%25%20more%20than%20the%20asking%20price%20but%20ask%20for%20that%20extra%202.5%25%20back%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20closing%20credit%20so%20they%20can%20pay%20their%20agent.%20Another%20buyer%20may%20offer%20the%20same%20dollar%20amount%20but%20ask%20for%20only%201.5%25%20back%20to%20pay%20their%20agent's%20commission.%20Yet%20another%2C%20like%20Dutta%2C%20may%20not%20ask%20for%20any%20money%20back.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20sellers%20should%20care%20about%20their%20net%20proceeds%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20that%20goes%20into%20their%20pocket%20once%20all%20the%20pesky%20fees%20are%20settled.%20They%20can%20say%20they're%20open%20to%20working%20with%20buyers%20on%20their%20agent's%20commission%20without%20backing%20themselves%20into%20a%20corner%20by%20suggesting%20an%20exact%20percentage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20buyers'%20side%2C%20saving%20money%20comes%20down%20to%20asking%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20request%20a%20lower%20commission%20from%20your%20own%20agent%20or%2C%20if%20you%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20it%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20ask%20for%20help%20from%20the%20seller%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-are-mortgage-closing-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclosing%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20ask%20for%20stuff%20that's%20not%20advertised%20and%20still%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Leo%20Pareja%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20brokerage%20eXp%20Realty%2C%20tells%20me.%20Buyers%20make%20special%20requests%20all%20the%20time%2C%20like%20asking%20for%20a%20repair%20or%20for%20the%20pool%20table%20in%20the%20basement%20to%20come%20with%20the%20house.%20A%20credit%20to%20cover%20your%20agent's%20commissions%20shouldn't%20be%20any%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20sellers%20these%20days%20are%20still%20offering%20to%20pay%20a%20commission%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agent%2C%20as%20they%20did%20before%20the%20settlement's%20changes.%20But%20buyers%20who've%20negotiated%20a%20lower%20commission%20with%20their%20own%20agent%20could%20use%20that%20to%20make%20their%20offers%20more%20attractive%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20a%20seller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20what%20has%20changed%20is%20that%20there%20are%20these%20sort%20of%20savvier%20buyers%20out%20there%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20high-cost%20markets%2C%20that%20are%20looking%20for%20any%20advantage%20that%20they%20can%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Bear%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20TurboHome%2C%20says.%20The%20company%20mostly%20operates%20in%20California%20but%20has%20recently%20expanded%20to%20Texas%20and%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20before%20they%20start%20eyeing%20homes%2C%20buyers%20should%20also%20do%20some%20due%20diligence%20on%20their%20prospective%20agents.%20Studies%20have%20found%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20buyers%20still%20want%20a%20professional%20to%20guide%20them%20through%20their%20purchase%2C%20which%20makes%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20massive%20transaction%20that%20most%20people%20will%20complete%20only%20a%20few%20times%20in%20their%20life.%20Some%20agents%20may%20be%20able%20to%20articulate%20exactly%20why%20they're%20worth%20every%20penny%20of%20the%20traditional%20commission.%20But%20there%20are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-realtors-reckoning-housing-market-home-sales-slow-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elot%20of%20agents%20out%20there%20vying%20for%20your%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20others%20may%20be%20willing%20to%20deviate%20from%20the%20standard%20commission%20to%20win%20more%20clients.%20One%20recently%20created%20portal%2C%20known%20as%20Fetch%20Agent%2C%20allows%20buyers%20to%20search%20for%20agents%20that%20match%20a%20set%20of%20parameters%2C%20like%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20location%20expertise%2C%20and%20even%20how%20much%20they%20charge%20in%20commission.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20buyer-agent%20commissions%20are%20no%20longer%20an%20afterthought%20but%20a%20key%20part%20of%20sale%20negotiations%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20shop%20around%20for%20an%20agent%20before%20shopping%20for%20a%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20offer%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20transparently%20see%20what%20an%20agent%20would%20be%20open%20to%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20a%20work%20arrangement%2C%26quot%3B%20Beau%20Correll%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Fetch%20Agent%2C%20tells%20me.%20That%20kind%20of%20transparency%20%E2%80%94%20knowing%20exactly%20what%20you're%20getting%20from%20an%20agent%20and%20how%20much%20you'll%20be%20paying%20for%20them%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20that%20could%20spur%20more%20agents%20to%20compete%20on%20price%2C%20which%20would%20bring%20down%20costs%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rollout%20of%20the%20new%20rules%20has%20undoubtedly%20been%20a%20mess%20%E2%80%94%20even%20now%2C%20a%20year%20after%20the%20settlement%20was%20unveiled%2C%20there%20are%20many%20different%20interpretations%20of%20what%20is%20and%20isn't%20allowed.%20But%20the%20idea%20that%20both%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20should%20think%20about%20commissions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20even%20negotiate%20to%20get%20a%20better%20deal%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20remarkable%20reversal%20from%20the%20old%20way%20of%20doing%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would've%20liked%20it%20to%20go%20further%2C%26quot%3B%20Brobeck%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20represents%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-sellers-realtor-agent-commissions-saving-rule-changes-lawsuit-settlement-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742371382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d9993ab8b41a9673faf850%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-sellers-realtor-agent-commissions-saving-rule-changes-lawsuit-settlement-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20year%20after%20a%20landmark%20settlement%20upended%20the%20real-estate%20industry%2C%20some%20savvy%20homebuyers%20are%20taking%20advantage%20of%20new%20rules%20to%20save%20big.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-sellers-realtor-agent-commissions-saving-rule-changes-lawsuit-settlement-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2