%2C%20while%20customers%20pre-booking%20the%20Xiaomi%2015%20will%20receive%20the%20Xiaomi%20Care%20Plan%20at%20no%20additional%20cost%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fxiaomi-15-series-available-for-pre-booking-in-india-pricing-offers-more-125031900383_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Suspends%20Some%20Efforts%20To%20Counter%20Russian%20Sabotage%20As%20Trump%20Moves%20Closer%20To%20Putin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESeveral%20U.S.%20national%20security%20agencies%20have%20halted%20work%20on%20a%20coordinated%20effort%20to%20counter%20Russian%20sabotage%2C%20disinformation%20and%20cyberattacks%2C%20easing%20pressure%20on%20Moscow%20as%20the%20Trump%20Administration%20pushes%20Russia%20to%20end%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20last%20year%20ordered%20his%20national%20security%20team%20to%20establish%20working%20groups%20to%20monitor%20the%20issue%20amid%20warnings%20from%20U.S.%20intelligence%20that%20Russia%20was%20escalating%20a%20shadow%20war%20against%20Western%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20was%20led%20by%20the%20president's%20National%20Security%20Council%20(NSC)%20and%20involved%20at%20least%20seven%20national%20security%20agencies%20working%20with%20European%20allies%20to%20disrupt%20plots%20targeting%20Europe%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20seven%20former%20officials%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20working%20groups%20told%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20inaugurated%2C%20his%20incoming%20administration%20was%20briefed%20by%20Biden%20officials%20about%20the%20efforts%20and%20urged%20to%20continue%20monitoring%20Russia's%20hybrid%20warfare%20campaign%2C%20the%20former%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20since%20Trump%20took%20office%20on%20Jan.%2020%20much%20of%20the%20work%20has%20come%20to%20a%20standstill%2C%20according%20to%20eleven%20current%20and%20former%20officials%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20requested%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20classified%20matters.%20Reuters%20is%20the%20first%20to%20report%20on%20the%20full%20extent%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%20effort%20and%20how%20multiple%20different%20U.S.%20agencies%20have%20since%20paused%20their%20work%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegular%20meetings%20between%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%20and%20European%20national%20security%20officials%20have%20gone%20unscheduled%2C%20and%20the%20NSC%20has%20also%20stopped%20formally%20coordinating%20efforts%20across%20U.S.%20agencies%2C%20including%20with%20the%20FBI%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20the%20current%20and%20former%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20could%20not%20determine%20whether%20the%20president%20has%20ordered%20the%20administration%20to%20halt%20all%20its%20work%20monitoring%20and%20combatting%20Russia's%20campaign%2C%20whether%20agencies%20were%20still%20working%20to%20hire%20additional%20staff%2C%20or%20if%20they%20are%20making%20their%20own%20policy%20decisions%20independent%20of%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20officials%20involved%20in%20the%20working%20groups%20said%20they%20are%20concerned%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20de-prioritizing%20the%20issue%20despite%20intelligence%20warnings.%20The%20change%20follows%20the%20unwinding%20of%20other%20Russia-focused%20projects%20launched%20by%20Biden's%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20last%20month%20ended%20an%20effort%20to%20counter%20interference%20in%20U.S.%20elections%20by%20foreign%20adversaries%20including%20Russia%20and%20put%20on%20leave%20staff%20working%20on%20the%20issue%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security.%20The%20Department%20of%20Justice%20also%20disbanded%20a%20team%20that%20seized%20the%20assets%20of%20Russian%20oligarchs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20not%20told%20career%20officials%20who'd%20previously%20participated%20in%20the%20effort%20whether%20it%20will%20recreate%20the%20cross-agency%20working%20groups%2C%20according%20to%20the%20current%20U.S.%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20U.S.%20is%20still%20sharing%20intelligence%20related%20to%20the%20sabotage%20campaign%20with%20European%20allies.%20UK%20government%20officials%20said%20that%20routine%20intelligence%20sharing%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20British%20government%20continues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20for%20comment%20about%20the%20suspension%20of%20the%20coordinated%20efforts%2C%20the%20White%20House%20deferred%20to%20the%20NSC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrian%20Hughes%2C%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%2C%20said%20that%20it%20coordinates%20%26quot%3Bwith%20relevant%20agencies%20to%20assess%20and%20thwart%20threats%20posed%20to%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20has%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20any%20attack%20on%20the%20U.S.%20will%20be%20met%20with%20a%20disproportionate%20response%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20at%20NATO%20said%20the%20U.S.%20was%20still%20coordinating%20with%20its%20allies%20on%20the%20issue%20but%20declined%20to%20offer%20more%20detail.%20The%20CIA%2C%20FBI%20and%20the%20State%20Department%20declined%20to%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnitta%20Hipper%2C%20EU%20Spokesperson%20for%20Foreign%20Affairs%20and%20Security%20Policy%2C%20said%20she%20had%20no%20specific%20information%20to%20share%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20suspension%20of%20some%20intelligence-sharing%20meetings.%20She%20said%20the%20EU%20was%20coordinating%20with%20NATO%20on%20countering%20hybrid%20threats%2C%20which%20span%20everything%20from%20physical%20sabotage%20of%20critical%20infrastructure%20to%20disinformation%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Policy%20Toward%20Europe%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pause%20in%20the%20cross-agency%20effort%20comes%20as%20Trump%20upends%20U.S.%20policy%20toward%20Europe%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20stirring%20fears%20among%20some%20current%20and%20former%20U.S.%20and%20European%20officials%20that%20Ukraine%20may%20be%20forced%20into%20a%20truce%20favorable%20to%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20Trump%20has%20made%20statements%20and%20policy%20moves%20appearing%20to%20favor%20Russia%20that%20have%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20both%20Democrats%20and%20some%20Republicans.%20But%20the%20president%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20spiral%20into%20World%20War%20Three%20and%20that%20improved%20relations%20with%20Russia%20are%20in%20America's%20strategic%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20agreed%20to%20a%20proposal%20by%20Trump%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20cease%20attacking%20each%20other's%20energy%20infrastructure%20for%2030%20days%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20said%20following%20a%20lengthy%20phone%20discussion%20between%20the%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%20told%20Reuters%20that%20reducing%20work%20to%20counter%20Moscow's%20hybrid%20war%20tactics%20would%20prove%20dangerous%20for%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20choosing%20to%20blind%20ourselves%20to%20potential%20acts%20of%20war%20against%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kori%20Schake%2C%20the%20director%20of%20foreign%20and%20defense%20policy%20studies%20at%20the%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%2C%20who%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20Trump's%20engagement%20with%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20Russia%20has%20recruited%20criminals%20in%20European%20countries%20for%20sabotage%20operations%20across%20the%20continent%20-%20including%20arson%2C%20attempted%20assassinations%20and%20planting%20bombs%20on%20cargo%20aircraft.%20Russia%20has%20also%20used%20influence%20campaigns%20and%20cyber%20operations%20to%20erode%20support%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20Western%20intelligence%20officials%20told%20Reuters.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20intelligence%20officials%20said%20the%20number%20of%20sabotage%20acts%20by%20Russia%20declined%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20but%20warned%20that%20they%20expect%20Moscow%20to%20continue%20its%20hybrid%20warfare%20while%20Western%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20pause%20in%20some%20of%20Washington's%20work%20to%20track%20its%20hybrid%20warfare%20campaign%2C%20Kremlin%20spokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20said%20the%20Trump%20administration%20was%20trying%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20%26quot%3Beverything%20ineffective%2C%20corrupt%20and%20implausible%2C%26quot%3B%20something%20he%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Bunderstandable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Western%20accusations%20that%20Russia%20commits%20sabotage%20in%20the%20U.S.%20and%20Europe%20are%20%26quot%3Bempty%20and%20ephemeral%26quot%3B%20and%20have%20not%20been%20proven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShadow%20War%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Russian%20forces%20streamed%20across%20Ukraine's%20border%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20Moscow's%20intelligence%20agencies%20launched%20a%20shadow%20war%20aimed%20at%20undercutting%20the%20U.S.-led%20effort%20to%20bolster%20Kyiv's%20resistance%2C%20six%20Western%20intelligence%20and%20national%20security%20officials%20told%20Reuters.%20Congress%20has%20approved%20%24175%20billion%20in%20assistance%20to%20Ukraine%20since%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow's%20efforts%20to%20retaliate%20against%20the%20West%20escalated%20in%20spring%202024%20with%20arson%20attacks%20throughout%20Europe%2C%20including%20one%20at%20a%20warehouse%20in%20London%20with%20connections%20to%20a%20Ukrainian-born%20businessman.%20Six%20individuals%20were%20charged%20with%20aggravated%20arson%20for%20that%20attack%20in%20a%20British%20court%20in%20November%3B%20at%20least%20two%20of%20them%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20accepting%20payment%20from%20a%20foreign%20intelligence%20service.%20A%20trial%20is%20due%20to%20begin%20in%20June.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20uptick%2C%20Biden%20directed%20his%20national%20security%20agencies%20to%20increase%20intelligence%20sharing%20with%20Europe%20and%20create%20task%20forces%20to%20combat%20Russian%20operations%20and%20ensure%20attacks%20did%20not%20occur%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20the%20former%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerican%20intelligence%20officials%2C%20working%20with%20domestic%20law%20enforcement%2C%20assessed%20that%20Moscow%20intended%20to%20target%20not%20only%20Russian%20dissidents%20around%20the%20world%20but%20also%20other%20civilians%2C%20including%20those%20helping%20Ukraine's%20war%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.S.%20alerted%20Germany%20that%20Russia%20was%20attempting%20to%20assassinate%20the%20CEO%20of%20Rheinmetall%2C%20a%20German%20manufacturer%20whose%20weapons%20were%20being%20used%20by%20Ukraine%2C%20two%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%20German%20law%20enforcement%20interrupted%20the%20plan.%20Rheinmetall%20declined%20to%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20late%20summer%2C%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%20set%20up%20in-person%20and%20virtual%20meetings%20with%20European%20national%20security%20officials%20to%20share%20intelligence%20on%20plots%20in%20Europe%20and%20to%20coordinate%20investigations%2C%20four%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20led%20to%20joint%20plans%20for%20addressing%20sabotage%20attacks%2C%20including%20procedures%20for%20arrests%20and%20a%20proposal%20for%20longer%20prison%20sentences%20for%20those%20convicted%2C%20four%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20memo%20drafted%20by%20the%20U.S.%20and%20Britain%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%20advocated%20that%2C%20among%20other%20steps%2C%20European%20countries'%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20work%20more%20closely%20to%20track%20criminal%20networks%20conducting%20the%20sabotage.%20It%20also%20proposed%20that%20European%20governments%20reduce%20their%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20Moscow%20to%20force%20Russia%20to%20cut%20its%20staffing%20in%20European%20embassies%2C%20two%20senior%20U.S.%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20those%20steps%20are%20still%20under%20discussion%20among%20European%20countries%2C%20one%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20said.%20The%20British%20embassy%20in%20Washington%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20its%20Western%20allies%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20currently%20in%20talks%20with%20Moscow%20about%20increasing%20Russia's%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20Washington%2C%20one%20current%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20said.%20The%20White%20House%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries%20about%20the%20memo%20or%20the%20move%20to%20potentially%20increase%20Russia's%20diplomatic%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20agencies%2C%20including%20the%20Cybersecurity%20and%20Infrastructure%20Security%20Agency%20(CISA)%2C%20have%20for%20years%20tracked%20Russian%20influence%20operations%20and%20ransomware%20attacks%20on%20U.S.%20critical%20infrastructure.%20Under%20Biden%2C%20top%20cybersecurity%20officials%20led%20an%20interagency%20team%20to%20share%20with%20European%20countries%20Russia's%20attempts%20to%20influence%20local%20elections%20and%20how%20to%20deter%20Moscow's%20attacks%20on%20national%20security%20systems%2C%20one%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20victory%20of%20far%20right%2C%20pro-Putin%20candidate%2C%20Calin%20Georgescu%2C%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20Romania's%20presidential%20election%20in%20November%20was%20annulled%20by%20the%20country's%20constitutional%20court%20after%20declassified%20Romanian%20intelligence%20reports%20indicated%20possible%20Russian%20interference%20-%20a%20decision%20criticized%20by%20Trump's%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance.%20Georgescu%20and%20Moscow%20have%20denied%20any%20meddling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECISA%20Deputy%20Assistant%20Secretary%20Tricia%20McLaughlin%20told%20Reuters%20the%20agency%20had%20placed%20on%20administrative%20leave%20personnel%20working%20on%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20on%20its%20election%20security%20team%2C%20without%20elaborating%20further.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcLaughlin%20said%20CISA%20%26quot%3Bremains%20committed%20to%20addressing%20all%20cyber%20threats%20to%20U.S.%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20from%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThreat%20To%20The%20Homeland%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20example%20of%20cooperation%20under%20Biden%2C%20the%20administration%20dispatched%20teams%20from%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20other%20agencies%20to%20help%20European%20countries%20investigate%20damage%20to%20several%20essential%20undersea%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20teams%20traveled%20to%20Copenhagen%20to%20help%20in%20December%20after%20Finland%20seized%20a%20tanker%20suspected%20of%20dragging%20its%20anchor%20on%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20floor%20to%20deliberately%20damage%20cable%20networks%2C%20one%20former%20and%20one%20current%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20said.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tanker%2C%20the%20Eagle%20S%2C%20is%20believed%20by%20Western%20intelligence%20officials%20to%20belong%20to%20a%20shadow%20fleet%20of%20ships%20Russia%20uses%20to%20evade%20oil%20sanctions.%20Russia%20has%20denied%20its%20involvement%20in%20a%20spate%20of%20cable%20incidents.%20Some%20Western%20intelligence%20and%20national%20security%20officials%20caution%20there%20is%20no%20smoking%20gun%20that%20signals%20Moscow's%20direct%20responsibility%20in%20all%20of%20the%20recent%20cable%20cutting%20incidents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20mid-2024%2C%20American%20agencies%20collected%20intelligence%20suggesting%20that%20Russia%20might%20detonate%20an%20incendiary%20device%20on%20a%20cargo%20or%20passenger%20aircraft%20over%20U.S.%20airspace%2C%20which%20provoked%20alarm%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20multiple%20former%20officials%20told%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20almost%20psychologically%20a%20very%20different%20threat%20than%20sabotage%20operations%20in%20Europe%20that%20were%20damaging%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20said.%20%26quot%3BBringing%20down%20planes%20is%20a%20whole%20different%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20was%20no%20clear%20evidence%20that%20Moscow%20formulated%20a%20plan%20to%20attack%20inside%20the%20U.S.%2C%20the%20FBI%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20crafted%20strategies%20for%20domestic%20agencies%20to%20increase%20screening%20of%20cargo%20entering%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20officials%20were%20so%20concerned%20that%20Biden%20directed%20Jake%20Sullivan%2C%20his%20national%20security%20adviser%2C%20and%20CIA%20Director%20Bill%20Burns%20to%20warn%20Putin%20and%20his%20top%20aides%20that%20if%20the%20campaign%20continued%2C%20especially%20inside%20the%20U.S.%2C%20Washington%20could%20list%20Russia%20as%20a%20state%20sponsor%20of%20terrorism%20-%20a%20designation%20that%20would%20further%20isolate%20its%20economy%20from%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20first%20reported%20the%20meetings%20between%20the%20Biden%20officials%20and%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20no%20attack%20has%20taken%20place%20inside%20the%20U.S.%20and%20the%20number%20of%20sabotage%20attacks%20in%20Europe%20dropped%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20according%20to%20three%20Western%20intelligence%20officials%2C%20who%20attributed%20the%20change%20at%20lea